A search and rescue mission is underway for a Gonubie man whose light aircraft went down in the Wild Coast area in the early hours of this morning. The man is believed to be John Waterson. Health department spokesman Sizwe Kupelo confirmed that a search was in progress. “This morning an Aeromed 1 EMS Helicopter is searching the Gonubie area. We have rescue crews are on the ground who are on alert and on standby,” he said. The aircraft has not yet been found. This is a developing story.